<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="180" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,402,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[199,454,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[199,454,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Malgassesia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation box="[672,846,510,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" refId="ref6943" refString="Le Cerf, F. (1922) Troisieme Contribution a l'etude des Aegeriidae. Descriptions d'Especes et Varietes nouvelles. Etudes de Lepidopterologie Comparee, 19 (2), 17 - 39, 190 - 191, pls. 539 - 540." type="journal article">Le Cerf (1922)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of two males from Brickaville. In the same publication, a third specimen, a quite different female from the same locality and date was described as the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[268,520,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Epitarsipus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufithorax">
<emphasis box="[268,520,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Epitarsipus rufithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[537,622,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Adult specimens of Madagascan Synanthedonini: 1–5. Rodolphia hombergi Le Cerf, 1911. (1–2) male, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (4–5) female, same data. (3) male, holotype of Malgassesia pauliani Viette, 1955, ventral view. 6–7. Malgassesia andrianony (Viette, 1982) comb. nov., male holotype. 8–12. Malgassesia rufescens Le Cerf, 1922. (8–9) male, Madagascar, Ihosy, Region sud de l’Ile. (10–11) female, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (12) female, holotype of Malgassesia biedermanni Viette, 1982. Scale bars 10 mm, ventral view right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1287075/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation box="[644,794,582,607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" refId="ref7296" refString="Viette, P. (1982) Insectes Lepidopteres Sesiidae. Faune de Madagascar, 61, 1 - 64." type="journal article">Viette (1982)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<typeStatus box="[932,1046,582,607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">lectotypes</typeStatus>
of both species and published the first correct description of the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[628,775,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[628,775,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a mating pair found in the “Environs de Tananarive” and a female from Bekily. He refers further to the misidentification of the female from Brickaville by Le Cerf and describes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" box="[424,609,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biedermanni">
<emphasis box="[424,609,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">M. biedermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
designating this specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[1015,1113,690,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">holotype</typeStatus>
and a second female from Tananarive [
<collectingRegion box="[289,448,726,751]" country="Madagascar" name="Antananarivo" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Antananarivo</collectingRegion>
] as a 
<typeStatus box="[513,613,727,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">paratype</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[676,774,726,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" box="[813,992,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biedermanni">
<emphasis box="[813,992,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">M. biedermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather badly preserved. It misses the antennae and anal tuft; however, significant differences between this specimen and the two well preserved females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[185,331,799,823]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[185,331,799,823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Tananarive and Bekily cannot be found (
<figureCitation box="[883,1017,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Adult specimens of Madagascan Synanthedonini: 1–5. Rodolphia hombergi Le Cerf, 1911. (1–2) male, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (4–5) female, same data. (3) male, holotype of Malgassesia pauliani Viette, 1955, ventral view. 6–7. Malgassesia andrianony (Viette, 1982) comb. nov., male holotype. 8–12. Malgassesia rufescens Le Cerf, 1922. (8–9) male, Madagascar, Ihosy, Region sud de l’Ile. (10–11) female, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (12) female, holotype of Malgassesia biedermanni Viette, 1982. Scale bars 10 mm, ventral view right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1287075/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
). Thus I consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" box="[1230,1412,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biedermanni">
<emphasis box="[1230,1412,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">M. biedermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[364,508,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[364,508,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
